            'Reach_Modifier' => '-2',
            'RT_Modifier' => '-3 RT'
        ) ,
        array(
            'Type' => 'Fall-back',
            'Description' => 'Moving away from the enemy, as well as turning away, changing grip or similar, to reduce Reach a lot.Falling back allows a Character to keep threatening someone who has stepped inside the reach of even the longest weapons. Additionally Falling-back while attacking can buy you time to recover, especially from battle strain or shock. ',
            'Rules' => 'The Character who falls back can either reduce their recovery time by 5 RT or 1 GRT, or the Character can Relieve 1 Shock (or 2 Strains) as they "fall-back", and the Character will either move weapon Reach metres "backwards" away from the enemy after the attack, or they may make an automatic disengagement action instead with Pips equal to the Reach, if engagement rules are being used. This Disengagement is usually bolstered with at least one Card from the Action.',
            'Required_Number_of_Profs' => '3',
