            'Description' => 'These thresholds indicate a Cartesian co-ordinate that specifies a position in some dimensional space, 1 dimensional for a single value, often 2d for surface maps and hex crawls, and even most dungeons), sometimes 3d (for realistic caverns and buildings), rarely 4d (time is included as well, key events begin or end Eras), occasionally 5d(branching time-lines and multiple choices can be represented this way). They are most often used to place Locations on a map (which will be referenced as well).'
        ) ,
        array(
